ardly possible that any natural defects in it should not be increased. The extreme sweetness of her temper must hurt his.\n\n- Jane Austen, Emma\n|\nThe word 'love,' used in connection with the reproduction of our species, is the most odious blasphemy taught in our times.\n\n- Honoré\n|\nFor every quote, there is one that challenges it.\n\n- R.\n|\nBefore tomorrow becomes your legacy, come the choices you must make today.\n\n- Bill Jensen, Future Strong\n|\nIf you expect the battle to be insurmountable, you've met the enemy.It's you.\n\n- Khang\n|\nLearn to uncrumple yourself, for life and people are always gung ho to crush you.\n\n- Vikrmn, Corpkshetra\n|\nA man's concern, even his despair, over the worthwhileness of life is an existential distress but by no means a mental disease.\n\n- Viktor E. Frankl, Man's Search for Meaning\n|\nThe mind confines our outlooks to a mere bundles of desires, pleasures, prejudices, and fears to safeguard the body it inhabits.\n\n- Rajeev Kurapati, Unbound Intelligence: A Personal Guide to Self-Discovery\n|\n...Many shadows hide behind light, and the best lies are those seasoned liberally with truth: salt covering the flavor of rotten meat.\n\n- Brent Weeks, The Broken Eye\n|\n...at seventeen I tried to write poetry confining myself solely to Anglo-Saxon words - don't know if it helped, but it made me more concrete ...\n\n- John Geddes, A Familiar Rain\n|\nWe can only change life in the country and radically reform society by having God’s wisdom, strength and authority\n\n- Sunday\n|\nBeginning is scary, exciting, terrifying, and all things amazing. Begin even when you're not sure.....What do you have to lose?\n\n- Chris\n|\nIf you truly love someone, you should be more interested in keeping them happy than in being right.\n\n- Stephen\n|\nI want to be a transitory fallen, lifted up by virtues every time.\n\n- Munia\n|\nThe view was in an unearthly way beautiful, but it was also unendurable. It implied too much\n\n- Robert Charles W